  "content": "<h1>Lecture Notes: Operating Systems Basics</h1><p>Key topics covered in Class 10 (June 2026). Check this before the exam on next Friday!</p><h2>1. What is virtual memory?</h2><p>Virtual memory is an abstraction layer that makes it feel like we have a massive pool of RAM, even if the physical chips are tiny. The OS swaps data block pages back and forth from the hard disk (paging files).</p><blockquote><p>Remember: Swapping to disk is extremely slow! Minimize swap thrashing by adjusting page sizing.</p></blockquote><h2>2. Key Concepts Checklist</h2><ul data-type=\"taskList\"><li class=\"flex items-start gap-2 my-1\" data-checked=\"false\" data-type=\"taskItem\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"><span></span></label><div><p></p></div></li></ul><ul><li><p>Page Faults: triggers an interrupt when RAM doesn't hold the page</p></li><li><p>TLB Cache: hardware lookup index for page translation</p></li><li><p>LRU Replacement: Least Recently Used eviction algorithm</p></li></ul><h2>3. TLB Cache vs RAM Lookup speeds</h2><p>Quick lookup times compared:</p><table class=\"border-collapse border border-slate-300 w-full my-4\" style=\"\"><colgroup><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Hardware Layer</p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Access Time (ns)</p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Cost / MB</p></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>L1 Cache Register</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>0.5 ns</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Very Expensive</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>TLB Index</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>2.0 ns</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Expensive</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Standard RAM</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>60.0 ns</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Moderate</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>SSD Page Swap</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>50,000.0 ns</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Very Cheap</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Focus on studying the LRU algorithm code exercises tonight!</p><table class=\"border-collapse border border-slate-300 w-full my-4\" style=\"\"><colgroup><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><table class=\"border-collapse border border-slate-300 w-full my-4\" style=\"\"><colgroup><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><table class=\"border-collapse border border-slate-300 w-full my-4\" style=\"\"><colgroup><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p></p></td></tr></tbody></table>",
